A binding is a name for a value.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    score = 10
    player_name = "Priya"
]

Beanstalk usually infers the type from the value.

Write the type when it makes the code clearer or gives the compiler needed
context:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    score Int = 10
    player_name String = "Priya"
]

Bindings are immutable unless you mark them as mutable. An immutable binding
cannot be assigned a different value later.
